For the purists, my version deviates from the recipe in the following way: I used 1 pound of ground sirloin in place of the pork shoulder, sweet Italian turkey sausage in place of the hot sausage, increased the red pepper to 1 tsp to compensate for not using hot sausage, and penne noodles instead of ziti (I used what I had on hand). That said, this was excellent; the sauce had a meaty, savory flavor, quite distinct from tomato-based sauces that might be used for lasagne. I was a bit worried that it was too watery, but once mixed with the pasta and baked, all the extra liquid was absorbed. This was a perfect recipe to bring to someone else's house, with no last minute steps required, and was gobbled up by 8 hungry basketball fans. I would like to try this with the pork sometime, but in a pinch, I think a variety of meats could substitute. I would try to undercook the pasta just a bit to avoid soggy pasta

