Rating: 4
this recipe has been reviewed many times and the reviews vary substantially. I think the biggest problem is sauces tend to vary and there is no precise recipe for a sauce in a recipe like this. We have made this twice. We loved it the first time but thought it a little dry also. The second time we made only 1 lb. of ziti and I made a few adjustments in the sauce: the biggest most important is a high quality can of tomatoes. We used imported plum tomatoes that were already chopped and in their own sauce; saved time and much better. Definitely the imported ones are far superior; we spend the extra money and buy them at a local Italian market. This produced a much bigger quantity of sauce. At first I thought it was too thin, but I simply took the cover off the pot for the second hour. No need for tomatoe paste. We also used a deeper dish for baking; the first time we used the suggested 10 X 15 X 2 but this time we used a 12 X 9 X 3; MUCH better in a deeper dish; covering the dish for part of the baking would also help. We have baked and indulged in many ziti recipes; its a staple in the northeast. We think this one beats them all! I believe we added a little extra pork too. In my mind this is a recipe well worth perfecting; it does freeze well making the sauce ahead of time as discussed in the recipe does make the dish simple.

