Rating: 4
Unbelievably good. It took me approximatly 3.5 hours to make this but it was well worth it. I used the spicy italian pork sausages and spicy pancetta. 1) Follow all the directions up to the two hour simmering. Before you simmer, add 6 ounces of tomato paste to the ragu stew and stir to dilute. 2)For the pasta, I used one pound of rigatoni instead. Make sure you salt the boiling water and add olive oil before throwing in the pasta. 2) In the buttered casserole dish, add the cooked pasta and HALF of the ragu stew and meat. Add 1/2 cup of mozzarella cheese and 1/4 cup of parmesan. Mix everything together. That way, after the baking is done, the mozarella and parmesan is between all the ingredients (big difference!). Add more mozzarella cheese (as much as you want) and then add parmesan cheese as well. Cover with foil and then bake according to the recipe directions. 3)After you're done eating the baked ziti, you'll have the last half of the ragu stew to mix in with another batch of 1 pound of rigatoni for baking. Repeat step #2 after you finish cooking the pasta to be added to the casserole dish.

